WEBVTT

00:00:03.730 --> 00:00:07.900
"to lead a rich,
fulfilling, happy life."

00:00:07.900 --> 00:00:10.230
But you cant always
get what you want.

00:00:10.230 --> 00:00:14.800
WOMAN: Is happiness an
experience that comes and goes

00:00:14.800 --> 00:00:17.060
or is it a state
that you can live in

00:00:17.060 --> 00:00:18.700
for long periods of time?

00:00:18.700 --> 00:00:20.560
I dont... I dont know.

00:00:20.560 --> 00:00:21.900
(screaming)

00:00:21.900 --> 00:00:24.100
"GILBERT: This emotional
life is a roller coaster,"

00:00:24.100 --> 00:00:26.530
taking us from the
heights of ecstasy

00:00:26.530 --> 00:00:29.360
to the depths of despair
and every place between.

00:00:29.360 --> 00:00:30.430
WOMAN: All emotions have a role

00:00:30.430 --> 00:00:31.730
in a healthy life.

00:00:31.730 --> 00:00:33.060
Were not automatons.

00:00:33.060 --> 00:00:34.730
"GILBERT: Im Dan Gilbert,"

00:00:34.730 --> 00:00:37.930
"and in this series,
Im going to introduce
you to everyday people"

00:00:37.930 --> 00:00:39.500
"who are searching
for happiness,"

00:00:39.500 --> 00:00:41.830
as well as to the scientists

00:00:41.830 --> 00:00:45.060
and clinicians who are
trying to help them find it.

00:00:45.060 --> 00:00:46.360
WOMAN: What Ive taken away

00:00:46.360 --> 00:00:48.460
is the resilience
of the human spirit.

00:00:48.460 --> 00:00:52.430
It is just amazing what we
can go through and be okay.

00:00:52.430 --> 00:00:53.860
(explosion)

00:00:53.860 --> 00:00:55.800
MAN: I thought I
was going crazy--

00:00:55.800 --> 00:00:58.300
"the dreams, the nightmares."

00:00:58.300 --> 00:01:00.330
But Im not letting it beat me.

00:01:00.330 --> 00:01:02.430
What more can I say?

00:01:02.430 --> 00:01:04.760
Im a happy camper. (laughs)

00:01:04.760 --> 00:01:07.360
GILBERT: Well see how our
greatest source of happiness

00:01:07.360 --> 00:01:09.960
lies in the people around us.

00:01:09.960 --> 00:01:12.630
"MAN: A basic need for
human beings is love,"

00:01:12.630 --> 00:01:14.100
is companionship.

00:01:14.100 --> 00:01:16.960
GILBERT: Well explore the
obstacles to happiness--

00:01:16.960 --> 00:01:21.300
"emotions such as fear,
sadness and anger."

00:01:21.300 --> 00:01:22.460
Have I lost it to the point

00:01:22.460 --> 00:01:23.600
where I did feel
like Ive lost it?

00:01:23.600 --> 00:01:24.700
Yeah.

00:01:24.700 --> 00:01:26.600
I went through like
six or seven years

00:01:26.600 --> 00:01:27.930
of real depression.

00:01:27.930 --> 00:01:29.960
I just was never quite
given the right pill.

00:01:29.960 --> 00:01:32.530
"GILBERT: But next, well
see what happiness is..."

00:01:32.530 --> 00:01:34.030
(laughs)

00:01:34.030 --> 00:01:37.560
what causes it and why we look
for it in all the wrong places.

00:01:37.560 --> 00:01:39.100
MAN: I won the lottery

00:01:39.100 --> 00:01:43.400
but being happy/content
takes work.

00:01:43.400 --> 00:01:46.230
WOMAN: I used to think that
things would make me happy.

00:01:46.230 --> 00:01:48.300
"Or money, success."

00:01:48.300 --> 00:01:50.460
Im realizing now that
thats not the fact.

00:01:50.460 --> 00:01:52.600
Happiness comes from within.

00:01:52.600 --> 00:01:55.030
And happiness comes from
experiences that we have

00:01:55.030 --> 00:01:56.660
with people that we love.

00:01:56.660 --> 00:01:59.960
